[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Analysis                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### ✅ Working SSRF Routes:                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `/app/main-website` → Returns 302 redirect (Flask app accessible)          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `/app/website-api` → Returns 200 with application data                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### ❌ Non-Working SSRF Routes:                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `/app/flask_api:8081/` → 404 Not Found                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `/app/flask_api/8081/` → 404 Not Found                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Implications                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **SSRF mechanism is limited**: The backend SSRF proxy only supports       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m specific/internal service names, not arbitrary ports or custom URLs          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **API service at :8081 is NOT accessible** through the SSRF interface     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Only pre-configured routes work**: The `/app/main-website` and          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/app/website-api` endpoints are explicitly whitelisted/proxied              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Conclusion                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The API service endpoint (`/app/flask_api:8081`) **does not work** for SSRF. [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The SSRF mechanism appears to be intentionally restricted to only the main   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Flask application instance, preventing access to the separate API service    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m running on port 8081. This is likely a security control limiting lateral     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m movement through SSRF.                                                       [32m│[0m
